explanations.machine learning: The paper discusses the use of gradient boosted trees (GBT) and multiple linear regression with feature interactions (MLRi) for building energy benchmarking, which are machine learning techniques.
explanations.supervised learning: The proposed models (MLRi and GBT) are supervised learning methods as they are trained on labeled data to predict building energy performance scores.
explanations.regression: The paper mentions multiple linear regression (MLR) and its enhanced version with feature interactions (MLRi) as methods for predicting building energy scores, which are regression techniques.
explanations.decision tree: Gradient boosted trees (GBT) are mentioned as one of the proposed models, which are based on decision trees.
